  "body": "**What would you like to be added**:\r\nThis change would change the semantics of `CSINodeInfo` from implicitly determining that a driver is installed based on the existance of the `CSIDriverInfo` inside the `CSINodeInfo` to determining whether the driver is installed based on a field `Installed` inside the `CSIDriverInfo` object.\r\n\r\n**Why is this needed**:\r\nThis allows us to see/read the information about the driver represented in `CSIDriverInfo` (specifically the `MigratedOnNode`) field even when the driver is not installed. The drivers required for CSI Migration (https://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/contributors/design-proposals/storage/csi-migration.md) will be pre-populated with `Installed: false` on [Kubelet startup (? TBD)]. This way we can seperate the two cases where the driver is not installed and:\r\na) MigratedOnNode == true\r\nb) MigratedOnNode == false\r\n\r\n/cc @saad-ali @bertinatto \r\n\r\n/sig storage\r\n/kind feature",
